Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> DATATYPE MAIN LPAR RPAR BEGIN stmtblock END
Rule 2     stmtblock -> stmt stmtblock
Rule 3     stmtblock -> <empty>
Rule 4     stmt -> decl
Rule 5     stmt -> assign
Rule 6     stmt -> whilestmt
Rule 7     stmt -> returnstmt
Rule 8     decl -> DATATYPE ID ASSIGNOP NUMBER SEMI
Rule 9     assign -> ID ASSIGNOP expr SEMI
Rule 10    expr -> ID PLUS NUMBER
Rule 11    expr -> ID DIV NUMBER
Rule 12    expr -> NUMBER
Rule 13    expr -> ID
Rule 14    whilestmt -> WHILE LPAR cond RPAR stmtblock END WHILE
Rule 15    cond -> ID GT NUMBER
Rule 16    returnstmt -> RETURN ID SEMI

Terminals, with rules where they appear

ASSIGNOP             : 8 9
BEGIN                : 1
DATATYPE             : 1 8
DIV                  : 11
END                  : 1 14
GT                   : 15
ID                   : 8 9 10 11 13 15 16
LPAR                 : 1 14
MAIN                 : 1
NUMBER               : 8 10 11 12 15
PLUS                 : 10
RETURN               : 16
RPAR                 : 1 14
SEMI                 : 8 9 16
WHILE                : 14 14
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

assign               : 5
cond                 : 14
decl                 : 4
expr                 : 9
program              : 0
returnstmt           : 7
stmt                 : 2
stmtblock            : 1 2 14
whilestmt            : 6

